<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911203-0027</DOCNO><DOCID>911203-0027.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- WTD Industries Inc.:   Revised Chapter 11 Plan   Accepted by Some Lenders</HL><DATE>12/03/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   WTDQC</CO><MS>BASIC MATERIALS (BSC)</MS><IN>BANKRUPTCIES (BCY)EARNINGS (ERN)FOREST PRODUCTS, PRODUCERS OF WOOD AND LUMBER (FOR)</IN><NS>BANKRUPTCY DECLARATIONS AND PROCEEDINGS (BCY)EARNINGS (ERN)RESTRUCTURINGS, RECAPITALIZATION (RCN)</NS><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)OREGON (ORG)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   WTD Industries Inc. said that it has reached an agreementin principle with some of its major lenders on the terms of arevised Chapter 11 reorganization plan.   The company said it intends to seek approval of therevised plan from its creditors and the court.</LP><TEXT>   The Portland, Ore., forest products company didn'tdisclose details but said that the revised plan willultimately allow for full payment to all creditors and leaveexisting common stock in place, though significantly diluted.The revisions, the company said, will not affect pendinglender liability claims of $30 million against WTD by FirstInterstate Bank.   WTD, which filed for Chapter 11 protection from itscreditors in January, also reported a net loss of $2.2million, or 35 cents a share, for its second quarter endedOct. 31, 1991, compared with a net loss of $8.8 million, or$1.42 a share, a year earlier.   The company posted second-quarter sales of $51.1 million,down 30% from the $73.1 million a year earlier. The companyblamed the quarter's sales decline on unusually dry weatherand forest fires, as well as the recession-induced decline inconstruction starts and lumber demand.</TEXT></DOC>